+# Trust Considerations: Solana Light Client
+
+### Solana's Design Philosophy
+
+```
+Solana's Trade-off:
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Gain: Extreme performance (50,000+ TPS)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Gain: Parallel execution
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Gain: Low latency confirmation (~400ms)
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Cost: No individual transaction provability
+```
+
+### Fundamental Architectural Differences
+
+While EVM provides two cryptographically provable methods (storage writes and event logs), Solana only supports account storage writes as a direct representation in the block hash. This creates fundamental differences in provability models.
+
+### Block Structure Comparison
+
+```
+// EVM: Dual Provability Paths
+Block Header
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ State Root ‚Üí Storage Slots (provable via merkle proof)
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Receipt Root ‚Üí Event Logs (provable via merkle proof)
+
+// Solana: Single Provability Path
+Block Header
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Accounts Delta Hash ‚Üí Account States (provable via consensus)
+    ‚ùå Transactions & Logs (not committed to header)
+
+```
+
+### Security Model Comparison
+
+```
+// EVM Log Path: Simple & Secure
+Transaction ‚Üí Event Log ‚Üí Receipt ‚Üí Block Header
+     ‚Üì           ‚Üì          ‚Üì          ‚Üì
+  (signed)   (deterministic) (merkle)  (consensus)
+
+‚úÖ Single atomic proof
+‚úÖ Causal relationship preserved
+‚úÖ Program authorization implicit
+‚úÖ Timestamp precision
+‚úÖ No state manipulation possible
+
+// Solana Account Path: Complex & Vulnerable
+??? Transaction ‚Üí Account Write ‚Üí Account State ‚Üí Block Header
+     ‚Üì              ‚Üì              ‚Üì             ‚Üì
+  (unknown)    (unverifiable)   (provable)   (consensus)
+
+‚ùå Multiple attack vectors
+‚ùå Lost causal relationship
+‚ùå Program authorization separate concern
+‚ùå Coarse timestamp granularity
+‚ùå State manipulation possible
+
+```
+
+### Limitations of Account State Approach
+
+```rust
+// What you CAN Prove:
+‚úÖ "Account X contained data Y at slot Z"
+‚úÖ "Account state was committed in block header"
+‚úÖ "Validators confirmed block with this account state"
+‚úÖ "Data was written by specific program" (via account owner)
+
+// What you CANNOT Prove:
+‚ùå "Specific transaction wrote this data"
+‚ùå "Data was written at exact timestamp T"
+‚ùå "Transaction was atomic with state changes"
+‚ùå "Historical state wasn't overwritten"
+
+```
+
+### Trust Model Analysis
+
+### EVM Events: Zero Trust Required
+
+```
+User ‚Üí Trust Level: 
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Cryptographic proofs (merkle trees)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Mathematical certainty
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ No external dependencies
+```
+
+### Solana Account Write: High Trust Required
+
+```
+User ‚Üí Trust Level:
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust validator consensus 
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust program authorization (application overhead)
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust no state manipulation (overwriting risk)
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust account derivation (application overhead)
+
+// Security Gaps:
+‚ùå Account can exist but verification required for:
+   - Which program wrote it?
+   - Was it the authorized program?
+   - Was it a malicious impersonator?
+
+‚ùå Not Atomic with Transaction:
+   - Account write could succeed even if transfer/action fails
+   - Transfer/Action could succeed but account write fails
+
+‚ùå Integration Overhead:
+   - Requires dedicated source-side interfaces/programs
+   - Complex application logic to protect PDA
+
+```
+
+### Polymer's Solution: Light Client Derivation
+
+```
+User ‚Üí Trust Level: 
+‚îú‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust validator consensus 
+‚îî‚îÄ‚îÄ Trust Light Client Derivation 
+
+‚úÖ Atomic with transaction execution
+‚úÖ Simple verification process
+‚úÖ Immutable once included
+‚úÖ Causal relationship preserved
+```
+
+Polymer's approach uses **light client derivation** that:
+
+1. **Verifies slot confirmations** to make sure it won‚Äôt reorg. 
+2. **Represents transactions** in a verifiable Ethereum-like trie structure
+3. **Publishes data** transparently on Polymer rollup and displays dashboard
+4. **Maintains protocol homogeneity** and scalability across chains
+
+This light client derivation keeps the protocol **homogeneous and scalable**. The next step is to **open-source this client derivation** so that anyone can independently verify and validate the committed roots, enhancing transparency and trust.
+
